By the Rational Root Theorem, any rational root of this polynomial must be of the form $\frac{p}{q},$ where $p$ is a factor of 1 and $q$ is a factor of 2.  The only possible rational roots are $\pm 1, \pm \frac{1}{2}.$  So there are $\boxed{4}$ possible rational roots.
