The sum of the interior angles of a convex $n$-sided polygon is $(n-2)\cdot 180^{\circ}$. Thus, the remaining angle must be $(n-2)\cdot 180^{\circ} - 1070^{\circ} = 70^{\circ}$.  This means that $n-2=70$, or $n=72$. There are $\boxed{72}$ sides.นวัต
