We want to find the constant term in the expansion of $(\sin x)^7.$  This is equal to the coefficient of $\sin x$ in
\[(\sin x)^7 = \sin^7 x + \binom{7}{1} \sin^6 x \cos x + \binom{7}{2} \sin^5 x \cos^2 x + \dots + \binom{7}{7} \cos^7 x.\]We want to eliminate the $\cos x$ terms, so we can use the identity $\cos^2 x = 1 - \sin^2 x.$  Then
\begin{align*}
\binom{7}{1} \sin^6 x \cos x &= \binom{7}{1} \sin^6 x (1 - \sin^2 x) \cos x \\
&= \binom{7}{1} \sin^5 x (1 - 2 \sin^2 x + \sin^4 x) \cos x \\
&= \binom{7}{1} \sin^4 x \cos x - 2 \binom{7}{1} \sin^3 x \cos^2 x + \binom{7}{1} \sin^2 x \cos^3 x \\
&= \binom{7}{1} \sin^2 x \cos^3 x - 2 \binom{7}{1} \sin^3 x \cos^2 x + \binom{7}{1} \sin^4 x \cos x \\
&= \binom{7}{2} \sin x \cos 3x - 2 \binom{7}{2} \sin^2 x \cos 2x + \binom{7}{3} \sin^3 x \cos x \\
&= \binom{7}{2} \sin 3x - 2 \binom{7}{2} \sin 5x + \binom{7}{3} \sin 7x.
\end{align*}Expanding $\binom{7}{2} = 21$ and $\binom{7}{3} = 35,$ this gives
\begin{align*}
\sin^7 x &= \sin^7 x + 21 \sin^6 x \cos x - 21 \sin^5 x \cos 2x + 35 \sin^4 x \cos 3x - 21 \sin^3 x \cos 5x + 21 \sin^2 x \cos 7x \\
&= a \sin 7x + b \sin 5x + c \sin 3x + d \sin x
\end{align*}for constants $a,$ $b,$ $c,$ and $d.$  Then $d = \boxed{35}.$ชีวิต
