In other words, $\angle APB = \frac{\pi}{2} - \angle AOP.$  The maximum value of $\angle AOP$ is $\frac{\pi}{2},$ so the maximum value of $\angle APB$ is $\boxed{\frac{\pi}{2}}.$  (The maximum value is achieved when $A$ and $B$ are at the endpoints of the track.)
